sentences: Loek Dikker (born 28 February 1944) is a Dutch pianist, conductor, and composer.
He gave his first jazz performance in 1960, in a jazz and poetry concert with Godfried Bomans.
He wrote his first film score in 1981, and has scored over sixty films.
Dikker is the founder and chairman of Muziekinstituut MultiMedia, an organization founded in 2006 to promote and encourage collaboration among multimedia composers.
Passage: A Richard Erdman Sculpture (1985) – documentary
South Side Ground Zero Boogie Blues (2004)
Golden Calf, for his body of work from 1985–1990
After training as a classical pianist, Dikker became a jazz musician after seeing a 1959 televised performance by Horace Silver and Sonny Rollins.
